  "text": "# Kubernetes RBAC Authorization Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\nThe Kubernetes RBAC authorization system is implemented across multiple packages in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository, providing a comprehensive role-based access control mechanism for API requests.\n\n## Core Components\n\n### 1. RBACAuthorizer (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go)\nThe main authorizer component that implements the `authorizer.Authorizer` interface. Key aspects:\n- **RBACAuthorizer struct** (line 50): Contains an `authorizationRuleResolver` field of type `RequestToRuleMapper`\n- **Authorize method** (line 75): Evaluates whether a request is allowed by visiting applicable policy rules using an `authorizingVisitor`\n- **RequestToRuleMapper interface** (line 37): Defines the contract for resolving policy rules (RulesFor and VisitRulesFor methods)\n- **RuleAllows function** (line 178): Checks if a specific rule matches request attributes (verb, APIGroup, resource, resource names, non-resource URLs)\n- **New function** (line 159): Factory method that creates a RBACAuthorizer with a DefaultRuleResolver\n- **RulesFor method** (line 129): Converts policy rules to authorizer rule info for admin-facing operations\n\n### 2. SubjectAccessEvaluator (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/subject_locator.go)\nComponent that evaluates which subjects (users/groups) can perform specific actions. Key aspects:\n- **SubjectAccessEvaluator struct** (line 42): Contains role/rolebinding listers and a RoleToRuleMapper\n- **NewSubjectAccessEvaluator function** (line 50): Creates evaluator with role/rolebinding data sources\n- **AllowedSubjects method** (line 64): Returns subjects that can perform an action by checking cluster-wide and namespace-scoped bindings\n- **RoleToRuleMapper interface** (line 30): For resolving role references to policy rules\n\n### 3. DefaultRuleResolver (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go)\nThe core rule resolution engine that maps users to applicable policy rules. Key aspects:\n- **DefaultRuleResolver struct** (line 91): Contains role/rolebinding getters and cluster role/rolebinding listers\n- **NewDefaultRuleResolver function** (line 98): Factory for creating rule resolvers\n- **AuthorizationRuleResolver interface** (line 37): Defines contract with methods GetRoleReferenceRules, RulesFor, and VisitRulesFor\n- **RulesFor method** (line 118): Returns all policy rules applicable to a user in a namespace by accumulating rules via visitor pattern\n- **VisitRulesFor method** (line 179): Visits each applicable rule by checking cluster role bindings and namespace-scoped role bindings\n- **GetRoleReferenceRules method** (line 240): Resolves a RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding reference to its actual policy rules (distinguishes between Role and ClusterRole)\n\n### 4. SubjectAccessReview REST Handler (pkg/registry/authorization/subjectaccessreview/rest.go)\nHTTP endpoint for checking authorization decisions. Key aspects:\n- **REST struct** (line 35): Contains an authorizer field\n- **NewREST function** (line 39): Factory for creating the REST handler\n- **Create method** (line 63): Handles SubjectAccessReview requests by:\n  - Validating the review spec\n  - Converting spec to authorization attributes\n  - Calling authorizer.Authorize\n  - Returning decision (Allowed/Denied) and reason\n\n### 5. Bootstrap RBAC Policies\nDefault RBAC roles and bindings created at cluster startup:\n\n**policy.go** (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go):\n- Defines standard cluster roles (system:masters, system:nodes, system:authenticated, etc.)\n- Contains helper functions and verb constants (Read, Write, ReadWrite, etc.)\n- Labels and annotations for bootstrap policy objects\n- API group constants for various Kubernetes APIs\n- ClusterRoles function: Returns default cluster roles\n- ClusterRoleBindings function: Returns default cluster role bindings\n\n**namespace_policy.go** (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/namespace_policy.go):\n- Defines namespace-scoped roles and bindings for reserved kube-* namespaces\n- NamespaceRoles function: Returns roles in kube-public, kube-system namespaces\n- NamespaceRoleBindings function: Returns namespace-scoped bindings\n\n**controller_policy.go** (plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/controller_policy.go):\n- Defines roles for Kubernetes controllers (attachdetach-controller, bootstrap-signer, etc.)\n- buildControllerRoles function: Constructs controller cluster roles and bindings\n- ControllerRoles function: Returns controller-specific cluster roles\n- ControllerRoleBindings function: Returns bindings for controller service accounts in kube-system\n\n### 6. Escalation Prevention and Policy-Based Storage\n\n**escalation_check.go** (pkg/registry/rbac/escalation_check.go):\n- **EscalationAllowed function** (line 31): Checks if user is in system:masters group (superuser exemption)\n- **RoleEscalationAuthorized function** (line 54): Checks if user has explicit \"escalate\" verb permission on roles/clusterroles\n- **BindingAuthorized function** (line 100): Checks if user has \"bind\" permission for a specific role reference\n\n**Role Storage** (pkg/registry/rbac/role/policybased/storage.go):\n- **Storage struct**: Wraps StandardStorage with escalation prevention\n- **Create method** (line 67): Uses ConfirmNoEscalationInternal to prevent privilege escalation\n- **Update method** (line 80): Similar escalation checks before updates\n- Allows escalation if EscalationAllowed or RoleEscalationAuthorized returns true\n\n**ClusterRole Storage** (pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrole/policybased/storage.go):\n- **Storage struct**: Wraps StandardStorage with escalation prevention\n- **Create method** (line 73): Prevents creating roles with rules the user doesn't have\n- **Update method** (line 93): Prevents privilege escalation in updates\n- Special handling for AggregationRule which requires cluster-admin privileges\n\n**RoleBinding Storage** (pkg/registry/rbac/rolebinding/policybased/storage.go):\n- **Storage struct**: Wraps StandardStorage with binding authorization\n- **Create method** (line 70): Checks BindingAuthorized and escalation via ConfirmNoEscalation\n- Prevents binding to roles with rules the user doesn't have\n\n**ClusterRoleBinding Storage** (pkg/registry/rbac/clusterrolebinding/policybased/storage.go):\n- **Storage struct**: Similar to RoleBinding but cluster-wide\n- **Create method** (line 69): Checks BindingAuthorized and escalation\n- **Update method** (line 94): Similar checks for updates\n\n**Escalation Validation** (pkg/registry/rbac/validation/rule.go and internal_version_adapter.go):\n- **ConfirmNoEscalation function** (rule.go:52): Ensures user rules cover the roles being granted\n- **ConfirmNoEscalationInternal function** (internal_version_adapter.go:27): Converts internal rbac types to v1 for validation\n\n### 7. RBAC REST Storage Integration (pkg/registry/rbac/rest/storage_rbac.go)\n- **RESTStorageProvider struct** (line 61): Registers RBAC storage with the API server\n- **storage method** (line 81): Creates policy-based storage wrappers for roles, rolebindings, clusterroles, and clusterrolebindings\n- **PostStartHook method** (line 131): Bootstraps RBAC policies at cluster startup via PolicyData.EnsureRBACPolicy()\n- **PolicyData struct** (line 143): Holds cluster roles, bindings, namespace roles, and bindings to be created at startup\n\n## Authorization Flow Summary\n\n1. **API Request** → Reaches authorization layer\n2. **RBACAuthorizer.Authorize()** → Uses RequestToRuleMapper to check rules\n3. **DefaultRuleResolver.VisitRulesFor()** → Finds applicable roles/rolebindings for user\n4. **RuleAllows()** → Checks if any rule matches the request\n5. **Decision** → Allow/Deny/NoOpinion returned to API server\n\nFor mutations on Role/RoleBinding/ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding:\n- Policy-based storage wrappers intercept Create/Update\n- ConfirmNoEscalation verifies user has permissions for rules being granted\n- EscalationAllowed/RoleEscalationAuthorized provide superuser/admin bypasses\n- BindingAuthorized ensures binding permissions are respected\n\nThis architecture ensures both flexible authorization and privilege escalation prevention in Kubernetes RBAC."
}

